e-article" fs-richtext-element=3D"rich-text" class=3D"resource-content w-ri=
chtext"><p><strong>In brief:&nbsp;</strong></p><ul role=3D"list"><li><stron=
g>An EIN number is an identifier issued by the IRS to U.S. businesses in or=
der to track their tax returns. All businesses in the U.S. =E2=80=93 includ=
ing charities and nonprofits =E2=80=93 must have a valid EIN before they be=
gin operations.</strong></li><li><strong>Verifying a business=E2=80=99s EIN=
 number usually involves cross-checking government databases, ordering repo=
rts from credit bureaus, and/or contacting the business directly.</strong><=
/li><li><strong>Automated third-party tools like Middesk draw data from the=
se sources in order to automate the collection and verification process.</s=
trong></li></ul><p>Nearly all businesses with operations in the U.S. need a=
n Employer Identification Number, or EIN, from the IRS before they can begi=
n functioning. As a company, finding out if a business has one is essential=
 for knowing whether or not it=E2=80=99s legal to take them on as a client =
or partner. But that=E2=80=99s only half the battle.</p><p>For instance, ho=
w do you know the business doesn=E2=80=99t have a new EIN because it recent=
ly changed its ownership structure? How do you know the company isn=E2=80=
=99t using another business=E2=80=99s EIN? How do you know the business=E2=
=80=99s EIN is even valid? These are all questions that must be answered by=
 cross-checking different data sources to verify an EIN number.</p><p>Fortu=
nately, as this article will demonstrate, there are tools =E2=80=93 includi=
ng Middesk=E2=80=99s <a href=3D"https://www.middesk.com/ein-database-search=
-tool">EIN database search tool</a> =E2=80=93 that aggregate data from mult=
iple sources to simplify and automate the process of verifying an EIN.</p><=
ul role=3D"list"><li><a href=3D"https://www.middesk.com/blog/verify-ein-num=
ber#what-is-an-ein-number">What is an EIN number?</a></li><li><a href=3D"ht=
tps://www.middesk.com/blog/verify-ein-number#how-to-perform-ein-verificatio=
n">How do EIN search tools perform EIN verification?</a></li><li><a href=3D=
"https://www.middesk.com/blog/verify-ein-number#how-to-verify-an-ein-number=
-for-kyb">How to verify an EIN number for a business</a></li><li><a href=3D=
"https://www.middesk.com/blog/verify-ein-number#ein-verification-lookup-too=
ls">EIN verification lookup tools that automate the process</a></li><li><a =
href=3D"https://www.middesk.com/blog/verify-ein-number#verify-businesss-ein=
-number-with-middesk">Verify more than just a business=E2=80=99s EIN number=
 with Middesk</a></li></ul><p>First, let=E2=80=99s back up a bit and explai=
n in more detail what an EIN number is, and why companies need to verify ea=
ch others=E2=80=99 EIN numbers in business-to-business relationships.</p><p=
>=E2=80=8D</p><div class=3D"w-embed"><h2 id=3D"what-is-an-ein-number">What =
is an EIN number?</h2></div><p>An Employment Identification Number, or EIN,=
 is a unique 9-digit identifier the IRS issues to U.S. businesses (includin=
g charities and nonprofits). It allows the IRS to easily identify a busines=
s for the sake of tracking tax reporting. All U.S. businesses must have an =
EIN in order to legally operate.</p><div class=3D"w-embed"><div class=3D"hl=
b dyk">  <div class=3D"hlb-header">    <img class=3D"hlb-icon" src=3D"https=
://cdn.prod.website-files.com/63beb0e2461232502d3d70a6/6729154c0a9bb48f3b62=
5bbe_hlb-dyk.svg" alt=3D"Did you know">    <p class=3D"hlb-heading">Did you=
 know?</p>  </div>    <p class=3D"content">      The term =E2=80=9CTax Iden=
tification Number=E2=80=9D, or TIN, is often used to refer to EINs. But TIN=
 is a more general term used to describe any identification number used by =
the IRS to track tax returns. So a Social Security Number (SSN) is also a T=
IN, albeit for individual persons. In contrast, an EIN is a TIN for busines=
s entities.    </p></div></div><h3>Why companies need to verify another bus=
iness=E2=80=99s EIN number</h3><p>In many industries, companies need to mee=
t strict <a href=3D"https://www.middesk.com/blog/know-your-business-kyb-ide=
ntity-verification-explained" target=3D"_blank">Know Your Business (KYB)</a=
> requirements if they wish to onboard another business as a client or part=
ner. This means checking that the business and its owners have legitimate i=
dentities, as well as weighing the potential risks of associating with that=
 business (including its owners).</p><p>A business requires a valid EIN to =
operate legally inside the U.S. (as well as perform some other financial an=
d insurance-related functions). So EIN verification is a small but importan=
t part of a company validating the identity of a business it wishes to onbo=
ard. That means ensuring the EIN is both valid and associated with the busi=
ness in question. If it isn=E2=80=99t, the company will want to rethink its=
 relationship with the business in order to protect itself from legal liabi=
lity and other risks.</p><p>=E2=80=8D</p><div class=3D"w-embed"><h2 id=3D"h=
ow-to-perform-ein-verification">How do EIN search tools perform EIN verific=
ation?</h2></div><p>There are a couple of places that EIN verification look=
up tools can draw information from. The most authoritative places are gover=
nment websites, such as state Secretary of State portals, the SEC=E2=80=99s=
 EDGAR system (for companies listed on public stock exchanges), or the IRS =
itself (for charities and nonprofits).</p><p>EIN numbers are always 9-digit=
 numbers in the format =E2=80=9CXX-XXXXXXX=E2=80=9D, so EIN verification se=
arch tools will check for numbers in this structure along with the business=
 name. The IRS also has a <a href=3D"https://www.irs.gov/businesses/small-b=
usinesses-self-employed/how-eins-are-assigned-and-valid-ein-prefixes" targe=
t=3D"_blank">list of valid EIN prefixes</a>, so automated tools can check t=
he first two digits of an EIN number to ensure that it=E2=80=99s legitimate=
.</p><p>Middesk=E2=80=99s <a href=3D"https://www.middesk.com/solutions/veri=
fication">Business Verification solution</a>, in particular, will look up p=
otential alternate business names if an EIN number matches but the business=
 name doesn=E2=80=99t. This allows for checking if the business has changed=
 its name (due to an acquisition, merger, or rebranding), or is potentially=
 using another company=E2=80=99s EIN (which is a big risk indicator). Midde=
sk can also help you manually find a match between a business name and an E=
IN if you=E2=80=99re having trouble finding it through the platform.</p><di=
v class=3D"w-embed"><a class=3D"cta-container" href=3D"https://www.middesk.=
com/ein-database-search-tool">  <div class=3D"cta-contents">   <div class=
=3D"cta-tag">EIN database search tool</div>   <div class=3D"cta-title">A fa=
st and reliable way to verify an EIN to assess the risk of your B2B relatio=
nship</div>   <div class=3D"cta-button">    <div class=3D"cta-button-text">=
Get a demo</div>   </div>  </div>  <div class=3D"cta-image-wrapper">   <img=
 class=3D"cta-image" src=3D"https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/63beb0e24612=
32502d3d70a6/682338b36ed507d99aa87707_cta-EIN-lookup.png" alt=3D"">  </div>=
 </a></div><p>=E2=80=8D</p><div class=3D"w-embed"><h2 id=3D"how-to-verify-a=
n-ein-number-for-kyb">How to verify an EIN number for a business</h2></div>=
<p>There are a few places you can find or cross-reference a business=E2=80=
=99s EIN. Just be aware that some are easier (and less expensive) to access=
 than others. Also, pay attention to dates on documents and for when web pa=
ges were last updated. There are certain circumstances in which <a href=3D"=
https://www.irs.gov/businesses/small-businesses-self-employed/do-you-need-a=
-new-ein">a business may change its EIN</a>, so ensure that you find the mo=
st recent one.</p><h3>1. Check the SEC=E2=80=99s EDGAR system</h3><p>One of=
 the first steps in verifying an EIN number should be to consult the Securi=
ty and Exchange Commission=E2=80=99s EDGAR (Electronic Data Gathering, Anal=
ysis, and Retrieval) tool. If a business offers its shares for trade on a p=
ublic stock exchange, it has to register and file reports with the SEC. So =
its information can be found in EDGAR.</p><figure style=3D"max-width:1216px=
px" class=3D"w-richtext-align-fullwidth w-richtext-figure-type-image"><div>=
<img src=3D"https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/63beb0e246123248d33d70ab/686=
f946b96946e69030a2d28_66b4120c5a07a23422369d05_6552982bc4b699fe66eeb8e5_sec=
-edgar.png" alt=3D"SEC EDGAR business filing search tool" loading=3D"lazy">=
</div></figure><p><a href=3D"https://www.sec.gov/edgar/search/" target=3D"_=
blank">Go to the SEC=E2=80=99s EDGAR Full Text Search</a> and type in a bus=
iness=E2=80=99s name, stock ticker symbol, or CIK number (Central Index Key=
, used to uniquely identify entities that have filed documents with the SEC=
=E2=80=99s database). You can also search for a specific individual associa=
ted with a business (or their CIK number), or a keyword in a document. Adva=
nced search options allow you to filter by filing type, filing date, and wh=
at state or country a business=E2=80=99s headquarters is in. Then click <st=
rong>Search</strong>.</p><figure style=3D"max-width:963pxpx" class=3D"w-ric=
htext-align-fullwidth w-richtext-figure-type-image"><div><img src=3D"https:=
//cdn.prod.website-files.com/63beb0e246123248d33d70ab/686f946b96946e69030a2=
d1e_66b4120b5a07a23422369cd2_6552984eeaf53b22c9bad357_sec-edgar-results.png=
" alt=3D"Results for a search for Alphabet Inc. in SEC=E2=80=99s EDGAR" loa=
ding=3D"lazy"></div></figure><p>The easiest place to find a business=E2=80=
=99s EIN is in its quarterly reports (10-Q) or annual reports (10-K). You c=
an filter for these types of filings by using the options on the left-hand =
side of the results window. Then select the filing you wish to view.</p><fi=
gure style=3D"max-width:792pxpx" class=3D"w-richtext-align-fullwidth w-rich=
text-figure-type-image"><div><img src=3D"https://cdn.prod.website-files.com=
/63beb0e246123248d33d70ab/66b4120b5a07a23422369cd5_655298775c7f76aa79badbf3=
_sec-edgar-filing.png" alt=3D"Sample filed document for Alphabet Inc. in SE=
C=E2=80=99s EDGAR" loading=3D"lazy"></div></figure><p>You should be able to=
 find the business=E2=80=99s EIN number near the top of the page. It will b=
e labeled on these types of reports as =E2=80=9CIRS Employer Identification=
 No.=E2=80=9D.</p><h3>2. Search a state=E2=80=99s Secretary of State busine=
ss directory</h3><p>Another traditional EIN number verification tool is a S=
ecretary of State business database, if you know which U.S. state the busin=
ess is registered in. Middesk has a <a href=3D"https://www.middesk.com/sos"=
 target=3D"_blank">Secretary of State website directory</a> that lists the =
Secretary of State websites for all 50 states, as well as D.C. Be aware, ho=
wever, that some states require registering an account and/or paying a fee =
to perform a Secretary of State business search.</p><p>Let=E2=80=99s use De=
laware, the state where Google was incorporated, as an example. Go to <a hr=
ef=3D"https://icis.corp.delaware.gov/eCorp/EntitySearch/NameSearch.aspx" ta=
rget=3D"_blank">Delaware Entity Search</a>, click in the box that says =E2=
=80=9CEntity Name=E2=80=9D or =E2=80=9CFile Number=E2=80=9D, and type in th=
e business=E2=80=99s name or registration number respectively. Then click =
=E2=80=9CSearch=E2=80=9D.</p><figure style=3D"max-width:713pxpx" class=3D"w=
-richtext-align-fullwidth w-richtext-figure-type-image"><div><img src=3D"ht=
tps://cdn.prod.website-files.com/63beb0e246123248d33d70ab/686f946b96946e690=
30a2d18_66b4120b5a07a23422369cdb_655298ab2adf02cc6d7fa03d_delaware-sos-sear=
ch.png" alt=3D"Business search interface on the Delaware Secretary of State=
 website" loading=3D"lazy"></div></figure><p>=E2=80=8D</p><p>Then just find=
 the business you=E2=80=99re looking for by name or registration number and=
 click on it.</p><figure style=3D"max-width:640pxpx" class=3D"w-richtext-al=
ign-fullwidth w-richtext-figure-type-image"><div><img src=3D"https://cdn.pr=
od.website-files.com/63beb0e246123248d33d70ab/66b4120b5a07a23422369ccb_6552=
98e6aa0159e0db3f5402_delaware-sos-search-results.png" alt=3D"Results for a =
business search on the Delaware Secretary of State website" loading=3D"lazy=
"></div></figure><p>Here, you can see the information file for the business=
; in this case, Google. But the EIN number is not included in this summary.=
 Note, however, there is an option to request a report that includes the bu=
siness=E2=80=99s tax assessment information; this will likely include the E=
IN. It costs $20, though, and you will need to create and/or log into an ac=
count to process the transaction.</p><figure style=3D"max-width:762pxpx" cl=
ass=3D"w-richtext-align-fullwidth w-richtext-figure-type-image"><div><img s=
rc=3D"https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/63beb0e246123248d33d70ab/66b4120b5=
a07a23422369cd8_655298fb701ed59fbac8ac58_delaware-sos-business-file.png" al=
t=3D"" loading=3D"lazy"></div></figure><p>Doing this manually takes forever=
. Watch our on-demand demo below to see how Middesk Verify can do this for =
you automatically=E2=80=94in seconds.</p><a fs-richtext-component=3D"gated-=
content-block" href=3D"https://www.middesk.com/events/productdemo-verify-ju=
ne-2025" aria-current=3D"page" class=3D"gated-content decoration-none w-inl=
ine-block w--current"><img loading=3D"lazy" src=3D"https://cdn.prod.website=
-files.com/63beb0e246123248d33d70ab/68233e7625481f31507b0096_combat-sytheti=
c-identity-fraud.jpg" alt=3D"" class=3D"gated-content_image"><div class=3D"=
gated-content_body"><div class=3D"gated-content_tag"><div class=3D"gated-co=
ntent_lead-text">Product Demo</div></div><div class=3D"gated-content_title"=
>Middesk Product Demo: Verify</div><div class=3D"gated-content_text">Watch =
the Demo Now</div></div></a><h3>3. Go directly to the IRS for nonprofit org=
anizations</h3><p>If the business you=E2=80=99re researching is actually a =
charity or not-for-profit organization, you can verify its EIN by going dir=
ectly to the IRS and its Tax Exempt Organizations database.</p><p>&nbsp;<a =
href=3D"https://apps.irs.gov/app/eos/" target=3D"_blank">Go to the IRS's Ta=
x Exempt Organization Search</a> and under =E2=80=9CSearch By=E2=80=9D, set=
 the option to =E2=80=9COrganization Name=E2=80=9D. Then click in the =E2=
=80=9CSearch Term=E2=80=9D box and type in the name of the organization you=
=E2=80=99re looking for. You can also filter results by database, city, sta=
te, and/or country. Finally, hit =E2=80=9CSearch=E2=80=9D.</p><p>=E2=80=8D<=
/p><figure style=3D"max-width:1222pxpx" class=3D"w-richtext-align-fullwidth=
 w-richtext-figure-type-image"><div><img src=3D"https://cdn.prod.website-fi=
les.com/63beb0e246123248d33d70ab/686f946b96946e69030a2d1b_66b4120b5a07a2342=
2369cde_655299c14363c856f96b6326_irs-teo-search.png" alt=3D"Search interfac=
e for the IRS Tax Exempt Organization database" loading=3D"lazy"></div></fi=
gure><p>You can see the EIN number of each match listed in the search resul=
ts. If you need more information, click on the name of the organization.</p=
><figure style=3D"max-width:1177pxpx" class=3D"w-richtext-align-fullwidth w=
-richtext-figure-type-image"><div><img src=3D"https://cdn.prod.website-file=
s.com/63beb0e246123248d33d70ab/686f946b96946e69030a2d24_66b4120c5a07a234223=
69cf7_655299d79a0fa6243f4b40d3_irs-teo-search-results.png" alt=3D"Results o=
f an IRS Tax Exempt Organization database search" loading=3D"lazy"></div></=
figure><p>Here you can see tax-related documents for the organization that =
the IRS has on file. Click on one to open a drop-down menu with more detail=
ed information, including sometimes a link to the actual document.</p><figu=
re style=3D"max-width:1136pxpx" class=3D"w-richtext-align-fullwidth w-richt=
ext-figure-type-image"><div><img src=3D"https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/=
63beb0e246123248d33d70ab/686f946b96946e69030a2d2b_66b4120c5a07a23422369d85_=
655299ef79999858e69d3480_irs-teo-organization-documents.png" alt=3D"Summary=
 and on-file document list for an IRS Tax Exempt Organization" loading=3D"l=
azy"></div></figure><p>Clicking this link will open a copy of the document =
that can be downloaded or printed. The document should have the organizatio=
n=E2=80=99s EIN printed somewhere on it.</p><figure style=3D"max-width:1027=
pxpx" class=3D"w-richtext-align-fullwidth w-richtext-figure-type-image"><di=
v><img src=3D"https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/63beb0e246123248d33d70ab/6=
86f946b96946e69030a2d31_66b4120c5a07a23422369d08_65529a045e27453ecca7caa0_i=
rs-teo-form.png" alt=3D"" loading=3D"lazy"></div></figure><h3>4. Request a =
report from a major credit bureau</h3><p>Another way to verify an EIN is by=
 ordering a report from a leading credit rating agency. Business credit rat=
ing information isn=E2=80=99t as private as personal credit scores, so majo=
r credit bureaus may provide copies of business credit reports on request.<=
/p><p>Not all credit agencies will provide the same options, though. Some, =
like Dun &amp; Bradstreet, will allow anyone to make an account and buy a r=
eport.</p><p>Others, like Equifax, will require you to be part of a company=
 and directly contact their sales team to request a report.</p><p>Also note=
 that not all credit bureaus will include a business=E2=80=99s EIN (or tax-=
related information in general) as part of their reports. So try to find sa=
mple reports to look for this information, and be sure to ask about the ava=
ilability of this information, before committing to any purchase.</p><p>=E2=
=80=8D</p><h3>5. Ask the business=E2=80=99s accounting department, or searc=
h other public places</h3><p>You may be able to verify an EIN number by loo=
king at a business=E2=80=99s written publications or other documents (such =
as letters or invoices), or somewhere on their website (try the =E2=80=9CAb=
out=E2=80=9D or =E2=80=9CContact Us=E2=80=9D page). If not, look for a phon=
e number or email address that can be used to contact the business. Try and=
 find one that can reach the accounting or payroll department directly, but=
 if not, ask to be put through to either of these departments.</p><p>Note t=
hat misuse of an EIN is a federal crime, so some businesses may be suspicio=
us as to why you want their EIN, or even reluctant to give it out. So send =
the request from a company phone number if possible, or from a company emai=
l address with a matching signature line; this gives the request a sense of=
 legitimacy. Thoroughly explain why your business needs the number, includi=
ng that it will be used only for KYB verification purposes.</p><p>Another o=
ption is to send the business=E2=80=99s accounting department a W-9 form. T=
his is an IRS form used specifically to request TINs (of which EINs are a t=
ype) in order to verify them for KYC or KYB purposes. It looks like this:</=
p><figure style=3D"max-width:1172pxpx" class=3D"w-richtext-align-fullwidth =
w-richtext-figure-type-image"><div><img src=3D"https://cdn.prod.website-fil=
es.com/63beb0e246123248d33d70ab/686f946b96946e69030a2d21_66b4120c5a07a23422=
369d0b_65529a6faa0159e0db404c26_irs-w9-form.png" alt=3D"" loading=3D"lazy">=
</div></figure><p>Once you have the <a href=3D"https://www.irs.gov/forms-pu=
bs/about-form-w-9" target=3D"_blank">template of the W-9 form</a>, fill out=
 the header section, leave Part I and Part II blank for the business to fil=
l out, and then send the form to the business.</p><p>This is a secure optio=
n because it requires sending the business your own company=E2=80=99s infor=
mation, and allows the receiving business to keep a copy. So the business c=
an trust that its EIN is being used properly because it knows exactly who t=
he request came from, and can report this information to the authorities in=
 the event the EIN is misused.</p><h3>6. Leverage an automated EIN&nbsp;sea=
rch tool</h3><p>There are certain third parties that are dedicated to compi=
ling information that businesses need for KYB. Middesk is one of them. Simi=
lar to the SEC=E2=80=99s EDGAR database, <a href=3D"https://www.middesk.com=
/products/verify">Middesk Verify</a> allows for searching businesses by the=
ir name and state. Then it=E2=80=99s a matter of finding the business recor=
d that matches, selecting it, and viewing the information.</p><figure class=
=3D"w-richtext-align-center w-richtext-figure-type-image"><div><img src=3D"=
https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/63beb0e246123248d33d70ab/686f94567081059=
cf433e508_65522954404fb9d96e885a64_middesk-occ-audits.png" alt=3D"" loading=
=3D"lazy"></div></figure><div class=3D"w-embed"><h2 id=3D"ein-verification-=
lookup-tools">EIN verification lookup tools that automate the process</h2><=
/div><p>Larger businesses that need to onboard and/or check many business c=
lients and/or partners in short order often don=E2=80=99t have time to do i=
t manually. Fortunately, there are several dedicated services out there tha=
t can check EIN numbers (and other business information) automatically to e=
nsure they=E2=80=99re valid and match the proper businesses. Here are a few=
 examples.</p><h3>1. <a href=3D"https://www.middesk.com/">Middesk</a></h3><=
p>Our Business Verification solution allows you to automatically lookup EIN=
s with an API so you can data ingested seamlessly, as well as many other va=
luable pieces of information for verifying the identities =E2=80=93 and ass=
essing the risks =E2=80=93 of businesses and their owners. These include sa=
nctions screening, registration documents, legal proceedings, digital footp=
rint, and more.</p><p>Business Verification contains over 91 million busine=
ss profiles from all 50 states (including DC), with data straight from stat=
e Secretary of State websites. It also automatically updates this informati=
on every 2 hours, so you can rest assured that you=E2=80=99re getting the m=
ost recent data.&nbsp;</p><div class=3D"w-embed"><a class=3D"cta-container"=
 href=3D"https://www.middesk.com/ein-lookup-api">  <div class=3D"cta-conten=
ts">   <div class=3D"cta-tag">EIN lookup API</div>   <div class=3D"cta-titl=
e">Middesk offers automatic EIN verification for 100% of registered busines=
